      "type": "web",
      "url": "https://www.alberta.ca/ohs-legislation.aspx"
    },
    "description": "The Alberta Occupational Health and Safety Act (OHS Act) protects most workers in Alberta.\n\nFederal workers, live-in caregivers, farmworkers, and others may have different laws.  These laws protect workers. \n\nThey are for workers and employers. The Alberta Workers’ Compensation Board (WCB) also covers most injured workers. "
  },
